The paper deals with a problem of computing a non-crossing matching of a set of points in the plane, which involves concepts from computational geometry (cs.CG) such as bottleneck matching and non-crossing matching. The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and the analysis of algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper presents an algorithm that involves some combinatorial techniques (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT).
